cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with improving the termination properties of Prolog systems with constraints, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of finite domain constraints and arithmetic evaluation, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents solutions to improve the reliability of Prolog systems, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
